{"id":76791,"title":"Epidemiology: measurement matters--making musculoskeletal disease count.","abstract":"Reliable estimates of disease burden support rational allocation of financial and human resources. Measurement is a powerful force for change as ‘what gets measured gets done’. The global burden of musculoskeletal disease studies ensures visibility of these highly prevalent, disabling diseases. Now we must act to reduce disease burden.","date":"2014-08-01","categories":"Nutritional and Metabolic Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24914694","annotations":[{"name":"Human resources","weight":0.585576,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_resources"},{"name":"Human","weight":0.495494,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human"},{"name":"Disease","weight":0.303001,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Disease"},{"name":"Measurement","weight":0.244841,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Measurement"},{"name":"Force","weight":0.20687,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Force"},{"name":"Finance","weight":0.101782,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Finance"},{"name":"Human musculoskeletal system","weight":0.047465,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_musculoskeletal_system"},{"name":"Resource","weight":0.0391252,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resource"},{"name":"Epidemiology","weight":0.0388889,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epidemiology"},{"name":"Rationality","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rationality"},{"name":"Count","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Count"},{"name":"Resource allocation","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resource_allocation"},{"name":"Visibility","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Visibility"},{"name":"Disease burden","weight":0.013127,"